<concept id="blackberry_ui_dialog" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Dialog</title>
    <shortdesc><i>The Dialog object contains functions for manipulating system dialog boxes.</i></shortdesc>
    <conbody>
        <p>The functionality in this object allows you to integrate standard system dialog boxes into your BlackBerry WebWorks Application and control your application flow based on user responses.</p>
        <example>
    		<fig>
    			<title>Screen shot showing a dialog box with one button.</title>
    			<image href="images/dialog_one_button.png" align="left">
    				<alt>Screen shot showing a dialog box with one button.</alt>
  				</image>
  			</fig>
  			<fig>
    			<title>Screen shot showing a dialog box with discard option.</title>
    			<image href="images/dialog_two_buttons.png" align="right">
    				<alt>Screen shot showing a dialog box with discard option.</alt>
  				</image>
  			</fig>
  		</example>
  		<example>
    		<fig>
    			<title>Screen shot showing a dialog box with a prompt.</title>
    			<image href="images/dialog_with_prompt.png" align="left">
    				<alt>Screen shot showing a dialog box with a prompt.</alt>
  				</image>
  			</fig>
  			<fig>
    			<title>Screen shot showing a dialog box with cancel option.</title>
    			<image href="images/dialog_ok_cancel.png" align="right">
    				<alt>Screen shot showing a dialog box with cancel option.</alt>
  				</image>
  			</fig>
  		</example>
  		<section>
	        <title>Installation:</title>
	        <p>To use this API in your project, add the dialog plugin:</p>
	        <p><pre scale="80">webworks plugin add com.blackberry.ui.dialog</pre></p>
	    </section>
